{"key":"post-9648426","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9648426</id>\n<content>If you're in the US, the electrical code requires two dedicated small appliance circuits to feed the kitchen counters and go nowhere else in the house.&amp;nbsp; Be sure to locate and use one of those, so you don't trip a breaker during use.&amp;nbsp; For example, it it was on the same circuit as a space heater, vacuum cleaner, or even kitchen blender, it would trip the breaker.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;That's an excellent choice if you're doing a lot of grain jars and/or spawn bags.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9649005</next>\n<prev>9648333</prev>\n<first>9647794</first>\n<last>9942259</last>\n<when>1232508078</when>\n<utime>01/21/09 05:21 AM</utime>\n</post>"}